<h2>INTRODUCTION</h2>

<h3>System Introduction</h3>
<p>The <b>SkillSwap</b> Mobile Application is a mobile-based application designed to simplify and support peer-to-peer skill exchange for users. It offers a convenient platform for finding swap partners, viewing skill details, communicating through chat, and scheduling learning sessions directly from a smartphone.</p>
<p>The app features an intuitive dashboard that displays your skill statistics and top match suggestions. Users can explore partners on the Discover screen, request a skill swap, chat with their partner like a messenger app, and optionally start voice or video calls. When a swap is accepted, users can schedule a session with date, time, and notes.</p>
<p>SkillSwap is intended for users who are <b>18 years of age or older</b>. Registration requires a valid date of birth. Accounts for minors are not accepted.</p>
<p>With its clean user interface and interactive functionality, SkillSwap enhances user convenience and promotes a faster, more organized skill-bartering experience. The app ensures that exchanging skills is straightforward, efficient, and accessible anytime, anywhere.</p>

<h3>System Significance</h3>
<p>The implementation of SkillSwap brings several key advantages to users who are looking for a streamlined and efficient way to learn and teach skills:</p>
<ul>
<li>Provides a mobile-friendly and accessible skill-swap platform</li>
<li>Simplifies the process of finding partners, requesting swaps, and confirming sessions</li>
<li>Enhances convenience by allowing users to chat and call partners in the app</li>
<li>Reduces the time and effort needed to find someone to trade skills with</li>
<li>Improves the overall user experience with an intuitive and clean interface</li>
<li>Supports optional AI-powered partner ranking and an in-app assistant</li>
</ul>

<p class="pagebreak"></p>

<h3>System Beneficiaries and Features</h3>
<p><b>Registered User</b></p>
<p>All registered users of the app benefit from the ability to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Create an account with name, email, birthdate (18+), location, and password</li>
<li>Add skills they can teach and skills they want to learn</li>
<li>Browse swap partners through the Discover screen</li>
<li>View match scores and skill compatibility details</li>
<li>Send and receive swap requests</li>
<li>Chat with swap partners through the Messages screen</li>
<li>Start voice or video calls from the chat screen</li>
<li>Schedule swap sessions after a request is accepted</li>
<li>Use the AI Assistant for guidance</li>
<li>Edit skill level and description after adding a skill</li>
<li>Disable a skill instead of deleting it (skills can be re-enabled later)</li>
<li>View schedule reminders for upcoming swap appointments</li>
<li>Rate swap partners from 1 to 5 stars and update ratings</li>
<li>Manage profile photo, bio, biometrics, and sign out</li>
</ul>
<p>Registration and login are required. Users must add at least one skill before they can request a new swap.</p>

<p class="pagebreak"></p>

<h2>GETTING STARTED</h2>

<h3>System Requirements</h3>
<p>To use SkillSwap, ensure your mobile device meets the following minimum requirements:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>Device Type:</b> Android or iOS smartphone</li>
<li><b>Operating System:</b> Android 8.0 (Oreo) or higher / iOS 13 or higher</li>
<li><b>Storage Space:</b> At least 100 MB of free space</li>
<li><b>Internet Connection:</b> Required for login, matching, chat, and calls</li>
<li><b>Permissions:</b> Camera and microphone (for profile photo and calls); biometrics optional</li>
</ul>
<p>For development or testing, the backend also requires XAMPP (Apache + MySQL), PHP 8.1+, Node.js, and Expo Go on the phone.</p>

<h3>Installation Guide</h3>
<p>Follow these steps to set up and run SkillSwap:</p>
<p><b>1. Start the Backend (XAMPP)</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Open the XAMPP Control Panel</li>
<li>Start Apache and MySQL</li>
<li>Run the database installer once: C:\xamppss\php\php.exe database\migrate.php</li>
<li>Open http://localhost/SkillSwapApi/public/api/health in a browser — status should be ok</li>
</ul>
<p><b>2. Run the Mobile App (Expo)</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Open a terminal in the SkillSwap folder</li>
<li>Run: npm install (first time only)</li>
<li>Run: npx expo start --clear</li>
<li>Scan the QR code with Expo Go on your phone (same Wi-Fi as the PC)</li>
</ul>

<h3>Using the App for the First Time</h3>
<p>Upon opening the app:</p>
<ul>
<li>You will see the login screen or splash screen</li>
<li>Tap Create an account to register (must be 18+)</li>
<li>After signing in, go to Home and tap Manage my skills</li>
<li>Add at least one skill you can teach or want to learn</li>
<li>Open Discover to find partners and tap Request swap</li>
<li>Open Messages to chat with your swap partner</li>
</ul>

<p class="pagebreak"></p>

<h2>HOW TO USE THE APP</h2>

<h3>A.1 Creating an Account (Registration)</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p><b>1. Open the registration screen</b></p>
<ul><li>From the login screen, tap Create an account</li></ul>
<p><b>2. Fill out the registration form</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Full name</li>
<li>Email address</li>
<li>Date of birth (must be 18 years or older)</li>
<li>Location (e.g. city)</li>
<li>Password (at least 8 characters)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3. Submit the form</b></p>
<ul><li>Tap Create account</li></ul>
<p><b>4. Optional biometrics</b></p>
<ul><li>After registration, you may enable Face ID or fingerprint for faster sign-in</li></ul>

<p class="pagebreak"></p>

<h3>A.2 Signing In</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p><b>1. Open the application</b></p>
<ul><li>Launch SkillSwap from Expo Go or your device</li></ul>
<p><b>2. Enter credentials</b></p>
<ul><li>Type your email and password</li></ul>
<p><b>3. Complete human verification</b></p>
<ul><li>Check Verify you are human and complete the puzzle if shown</li></ul>
<p><b>4. Sign in</b></p>
<ul><li>Tap Sign in to enter the app</li></ul>

<h3>A.3 Home Dashboard</h3>
<p>When you sign in, the Home tab shows:</p>
<ul>
<li>Welcome message with your name</li>
<li>Stats: skills offered, skills wanted, pending swaps, active swaps</li>
<li>Manage my skills button</li>
<li>Top matches preview with link to Discover</li>
</ul>

<p class="pagebreak"></p>

<h3>B.1 Managing Your Skills (Add, Edit, Disable)</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p class="step"><b>1. Open My Skills</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• From Home, tap <b>Manage my skills</b> — or from Profile, tap <b>My Skills</b>.</p>
<p class="step"><b>2. Add a skill</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Select <b>I can teach</b> or <b>I want to learn</b>.</p>
<p class="step-sub">• Enter skill name and level, then tap <b>Add skill</b>.</p>
<p class="step"><b>3. Edit a skill</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Tap the <b>pencil (edit)</b> icon next to an active skill.</p>
<p class="step-sub">• Change the level or description, then tap <b>Save</b>.</p>
<p class="step"><b>4. Disable a skill (not delete)</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Tap the <b>eye-off</b> icon next to a skill.</p>
<p class="step-sub">• Confirm <b>Disable</b>. The skill is hidden from matching but kept in your profile.</p>
<p class="step"><b>5. Re-enable a disabled skill</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Under <b>Disabled skills</b>, tap the <b>refresh</b> icon to enable it again.</p>
<p><b>Important:</b> You must have at least one <b>active</b> skill before you can request a swap on Discover.</p>

<h3>B.2 Discovering Swap Partners</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p><b>1. Open Discover</b></p>
<ul><li>Tap the Discover tab at the bottom of the screen</li></ul>
<p><b>2. Browse partners</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Scroll through suggested swap partners</li>
<li>View match score, skills they offer, and skills they want</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3. Request a swap</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Tap Request swap on a partner card</li>
<li>Tap Open chat in the confirmation dialog, or find the chat later in Messages</li>
</ul>
<p><b>4. If swap already sent</b></p>
<ul><li>The button changes to Open chat — tap it to continue the conversation</li></ul>

<p class="pagebreak"></p>

<h3>C.1 Messages and Chat</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p><b>1. Open Messages</b></p>
<ul><li>Tap the Messages tab</li></ul>
<p><b>2. Select a swap</b></p>
<ul><li>Tap a partner name to open the chat</li></ul>
<p><b>3. Send messages</b></p>
<ul><li>Type in the message box and tap the send button</li></ul>
<p><b>4. Accept or decline requests</b></p>
<ul><li>If someone sent you a request, tap Accept or Decline on the Messages list</li></ul>

<h3>C.2 Voice and Video Calls</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p><b>1. Open a chat</b></p>
<ul><li>Go to Messages and open a conversation</li></ul>
<p><b>2. Start a call</b></p>
<ul>
<li>Tap the phone icon for a voice call</li>
<li>Tap the video camera icon for a video call</li>
</ul>
<p><b>3. Join the call</b></p>
<ul><li>Your partner opens the same chat and taps the same call button to join</li></ul>

<h3>C.3 Scheduling a Swap Session</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p><b>1. Accept the swap first</b></p>
<ul><li>Scheduling is available only when the swap status is accepted</li></ul>
<p><b>2. Open the chat and tap Schedule</b></p>
<ul><li>Enter date and time (e.g. 2026-07-01 15:00)</li></ul>
<p><b>3. Add notes (optional)</b></p>
<ul><li>Describe what you will cover in the session</li></ul>
<p><b>4. Confirm</b></p>
<ul><li>Tap Confirm session — view upcoming sessions on Profile</li></ul>

<p class="pagebreak"></p>

<h3>C.4 View Schedule Reminders</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p class="step"><b>1. Open reminders from Home</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Tap <b>View schedule reminders</b> on the Home dashboard.</p>
<p class="step"><b>2. Or open from Profile</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Go to Profile → <b>Upcoming sessions</b> → tap <b>View all reminders</b>.</p>
<p class="step"><b>3. Read appointment details</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Each reminder shows a label such as <b>Today</b>, <b>Tomorrow</b>, or <b>In 3 days</b>.</p>
<p class="step-sub">• Tap a reminder to open the related swap chat.</p>

<h3>C.5 Update Partner Ratings</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p class="step"><b>1. Open an accepted swap chat</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Ratings are available only when the swap status is <b>accepted</b>.</p>
<p class="step"><b>2. Select stars</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Tap 1 to 5 stars to rate your swap partner.</p>
<p class="step"><b>3. Submit or update</b></p>
<p class="step-sub">• Tap <b>Submit rating</b> or <b>Update rating</b> to save your score.</p>
<p class="step-sub">• You can change your rating at any time.</p>

<p class="pagebreak"></p>

<h3>D.1 AI Assistant</h3>
<p><b>Steps:</b></p>
<p><b>1. Open the AI tab</b></p>
<ul><li>Tap AI at the bottom of the screen</li></ul>
<p><b>2. Ask a question</b></p>
<ul><li>Type a message about skills, swapping, or learning</li></ul>
<p><b>3. View the reply</b></p>
<ul><li>The assistant responds using Google Gemini when configured</li></ul>

<h3>D.2 Profile and Account Settings</h3>
<p>From the Profile tab you can:</p>
<ul>
<li>Change profile photo (gallery or camera)</li>
<li>Edit and save your bio</li>
<li>Enable or disable Face ID / fingerprint sign-in</li>
<li>Open My Skills and AI Assistant</li>
<li>View upcoming sessions</li>
<li>Sign out</li>
</ul>

<p class="pagebreak"></p>

